Results for the Bauchi South senatorial district bye-election from four local government areas so far announced indicated that the All Progressives Congress (APC) has won in three. APC won in Dass, Kirfi and Toro local government areas while the opposition Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) won in Bogoro, the local government where the Speaker of the House of Representatives, Yakubu Dogara, came from. The APC won with 7,432 votes in Dass, 11,051 in Kirfi and 30,658 votes in Toro. PDP won in Bogoro with 6,646 votes against APC's 3,992 The results of Bauchi, Alkaleri and Tafawa Balewa are still being awaited as at press time.  Details later...